1. C-x C-s: Save a working file
2. C-x C-w: Save as new file
3. C-x C-f file_name: Find and open file_name
C-x C-f without absolute path to file_name => Enter => Travese directory
4. C-x C-c: Exit emacs
5. M-<: Move cursor to the Top of the file
6. M->: Move cursor to the End of the file
7. C-v: Next screen (Page down)
8. M-v: Previous screen (Page up)
9. C-a: Start of current line
10. C-e: End of current line
11. M-f: Forward 1 word
12. M-b: Backward 1 word
13. M-x goto-line: Go to a specific line
--------------
14. C-spacebar: Hightlight the block of text => Ready to cut/copy
15. M-w: Copy
16. C-y: Paste
17. C-w: Delete
--------------
18. C-x 1: 1 window
19. C-x 2: Split screen into 2 horizontal screen
20. C-x 3: Add a new vertical window
21. C-x o: Move cursor to the bottom of 'the next' window
22. C-x 0: Dismiss window
--------------
23. C-s: Search forward string
24. C-r: Search backward String
25. M-%: Replace String
--------------
26. C-x u: Undo
